    <text id="B1258T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Brower requests that Edward Brooks be discharged from the hospital so "that the
                    government may be relieved of the expense of his support." Jordan investigates
                    the possibility that Brooks' son, living near Staunton, is willing and able to
                    support him.</p>
            </div1>
            <div1 type="section" id="wrapper">
                <p>Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">R.F. &amp; A.L.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Headquarters">Hd Qrs.</abbr> 9th Sub <abbr expan="District">Dist.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr>, Winchester, May 30/68<lb/>Respectfully
                    referred to <hi rend="underline">J.W. Jordan</hi>
                    <abbr expan="Assistant Sub Assistant Commissioner">A.S.A.C.</abbr> for report as
                    to ability and willingness of <hi rend="underline">Edward Brooks, Jr.</hi> to
                    support his father.<lb/>John A. McDonnell<lb/>Sub <abbr
                        expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst. Comr.</abbr></p>

                <p>Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">R.F. and A.
                    Lands</abbr>, Office 4 <abbr expan="Division">D.</abbr> 9th Sub <abbr
                        expan="District">Dist.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Virgnia">Va.</abbr>, Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr>
                    June 15th 1868<lb/>Respectfully returned to Captain <hi rend="underline">Jno. A.
                        McDonnell</hi>, <abbr expan="Sub Assistant Commissioner">S.A.C.</abbr> 9th
                        <abbr expan="District">Dist.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr> with the remark, that upon investigation, I
                    find that the within named <hi rend="underline">Edward Brooks</hi> is a
                    reliable, industrious man employed at good wages, is married, and has a large
                    family to support. He is willing and I presume can provide for his father. He
                    resides about six miles from Staunton, and in the event the father is sent here,
                    I would suggest that the son be notified (through <hi rend="underline">this</hi>
                    office) as to the date &amp;c upon which the father will leave
                        Richmond.<lb/><abbr expan="John">Jno.</abbr> W. Jordan<lb/><abbr
                        expan="Assistant Sub Assistant Commissioner">Asst. Sub Asst. Comr.</abbr>,
                    4th <abbr expan="Division">Divn</abbr>, 9th <abbr expan="Sub-District">S. Dist.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d5">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d6">
                <head>
                    Howards Grove Hospital
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Brevet Lieutenant Colonel">Bvt. Lieut.
                        Col.</abbr> J. J. DeLamater, <abbr expan="United States Infantry"
                            >U.S.I.</abbr><lb/><abbr expan="Surgeon">Surg.</abbr> in <abbr
                            expan="chief">chf.</abbr> Bureau <abbr
                            expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">R. F. and A.
                        L.</abbr><lb/>District of Virginia</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-05-27">May 27th 1868</date>
                        <name type="place">Richmond, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>
                        <abbr expan="Colonel">Col.</abbr>
                    </salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have the honor to request transportation to Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia"
                        >Va.</abbr> for Edward Brooks, Sr. aged sixty-eight, an indigent inmate of
                    this Hospital, from Augusta <abbr expan="County">Co.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr> in order that the government may be relieved
                    of the expense of his support.</p>

                <p>His son, Edward Brooks, living in Middle Brooke, near Staunton, <abbr
                        expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr> pledging himself to support him.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>I have the honor to be, Colonel<lb/>Very Respectfully, Your <abbr
                            expan="Obedient Servant">Obet. Servt.</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>D. R. Brower<lb/><abbr
                            expan="Acting Assistant Surgeon, United States Army">Actg. Asst. Surg.
                            USA</abbr><lb/>In charge of Hospital</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
